name: Ext.sparkline.Line
doc:
Plots a line graph based upon the input values array.

See the base class for a simple example.

members.name: chartRangeMax
members.doc: The maximum value to use for the range of Y values of the chart - Defaults to the minimum value supplied.

members.name: chartRangeMaxX
members.doc: The maximum value to use for the X value of the chart.

members.name: chartRangeMin
members.doc: The minimum value to use for the range of Y values of the chart - Defaults to the minimum value supplied.

members.name: chartRangeMinX
members.doc: The minimum value to use for the X value of the chart.

An XTemplate used to display the value or values in a tooltip when hovering over a Sparkline.

The implemented subclases all define their own tipTpl, but it can be overridden.

members.name: valueSpots
members.doc:
An object which uses range specifiers as keys to indicate spot color values for range of values. A range specifier is of the form [number]:[number] indicating start and end range. Omitting aither means an open ended range. For example to render green spots on all values less than 50 and red on values higher than 50 use:

{ // Open ended range, with max value 49 ":49": "green",

   // Open ended range, with min value 50
   "50:": "red"

}
members.short_doc:
An object which uses range specifiers as keys to indicate spot color values
for range of values. ...
